snippet.textDisplay:
If they do this with weapons fine, but give me back my Destiny 1 planets, strikes, raids, crucible maps, archons forge, court of oryx, gunsmith arms day. It looks like strike and pvp specific loot is coming back, which is great news.


I keep says this but bungie could easily sell a branded destiny 500gb external HDD for 20-30 bucks so all the game fits on there, remove these technical limitations and stop taking things away from us.


All those new light players would have so much content if the two games were combined and og destiny gamers are, for the most part, enough nostalgic enough now to not complain about 'i've done this before'. Everything we do in destiny is essentially what we've done before anyway, difference is they took a lot of stuff away. D2 should exist, it was right to build a (slightly) newer Tiger engine (Destiny's game architecture, like the Unreal engine) but now the destiny 1 stuff is a gaping hole in the core game experience which is as good, if not better than what replaced it in D2.

snippet.textDisplay:
I appreciate the game since 2015 but I have my doubts if Bungie is still able to bring new content and follow up on the game's Lore in a rich and consistent way.
As for the return of the Osiris Challenge, I have nothing against it, because I enjoyed it on D1. However, I expected a little more whim from Bungie, because I know that they are capable of doing it, involve a new lore, link at least with the current season, among other things. But if they didn't and are just re-ordering an old package, I'm sorry for that!
I hope that at least they have more caprice in the Lore of the Digno season, in case it is called that ...
When playing something for a long time, whether you are a casual or pro player, focused on PVP or PVE, something more is expected from the game that is already entering its 6th year.


P.S. My voice is unique, but it is not lonely. I have been a member of this community for years, I appreciate and play the game, so I wish it to continue with all its strength in its full capacity.
We all know that Bungie is capable of doing better, but we have to remind her of that. Otherwise, it will be just one more slot machine that deceives its fanboys.

snippet.textDisplay: I love destiny, trust me. I have plenty hours of play and I keep Playing everyday. Even I am not a pvp player in video game in general, I honestly don't think power level should be enabled. Trials is about skill and having good weapons, not the best lvl. People who play 8 hours a day, every day will have a huge advantage over casual. Just make sure the good weapons are accessible too everyone. Also even if I don't like pvp in games in general, I feel disappointed to see old gear for reward. Feels kind of lazy to me. Even if it's cool and all, I hope it's not the end game loot try hards will get. Even if this season will not be for me, I am happy to see bungie make something that the majority wanted. Keep it up!

snippet.textDisplay:
Everyone going to LFG team farming lost sectors hard next season with "Power Enabled". After this last IB playing against high 990+ to 1000+ being in the low to mid 980 myself there is a noticeable TTK difference. Some of those players tanked a point blank Mindbender's while I get OHK after landing my shot first and receiving theirs' a second later. I was also getting downed really quick by their primaries also. I didn't get it at first then I looked at the opponents power level and saw the big numbers. Not hating on those guardians because it's within IB.


I believe power enabled is to prevent free Steam cheating accounts, but I'm looking forward to all the Crucible only content creators crying and seeing when Bungo will cater to them like always. To me D2 Yr3 is meant for content creators and Eververse purchases.

snippet.textDisplay: Since d1 beta I have played this game and they keep just ruining it. I'm sick of playing a game I once and still really want play but is just a shadow of its original self. I play pvp and grind for weapon rolls I want and even tho this means doing almost all of the games modes and activities in game like forges and sundial I still dont gain any reasonable amount of light. This game csnt be watered down by making it easier I agree but why make things unnecessarily impossible to achieve. Save iron banner for the people who have the time and friends in there life to constantly grind raid and hard pvp content. Please don't take trials out of my grasp. I miss it and desperately want that feeling back please.
